4, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"golds\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"20 years\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"a disappointing seventh place\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 869}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal table\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet Grainger, chair ofUK Sport, the government agency responsible for distributing funding to elite sports, believes the feelgood factor generated by the home Games 12 years ago is still very much in evidence.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Grainger\", \"score\": 0.9999966098731132, \"rank\": 3.1628203695607647e-06, \"text\": \"Grainger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Grainger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Grainger\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the government agency\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 981}, {\"ngram\": \"elite sports\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"the feelgood factor\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"the home Games\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The former rower, a five-time Olympian herself and gold medallist in London, told the PA news agency: \\\"I am not one of the people who find it, in any way, a bad result.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999999894574563, \"rank\": 1.0542508925517541e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999998173937168, \"rank\": 1.0862849879020096e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The former rower\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1118}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medallist\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"the PA news agency\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"any way\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You have got 65 medals across 18 sports, and that was the real aim.\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"65 medals\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"18 sports\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the real aim\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medal range was 50-70, so to end up with 65 is fantastic.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1402, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medal range\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are only three nations that have produced over 60 medals in the last four games, and that's GB, USA and China.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.7674716766627229, \"rank\": 0.2999427939069471, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998558175961838, \"rank\": 0.00010980419086650291, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1515, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9990641457020922, \"rank\": 0.0004309238422850264, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only three nations\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"over 60 medals\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"the last four games\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be in that group of nations is amazing for a relatively small country.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that group\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"a relatively small country\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In 2012 there was such an incredible build-up to the home Games and there was a sense of, once we have done that, will we be finished with sport?\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such an incredible build-up\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"the home Games\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"a sense\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1742}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Then what you have seen is this incredible hunger and desire for a very new generation of athletes to build their own part of the story, and to write another chapter - and to see there is more success to come.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this incredible hunger\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1795}, {\"ngram\": \"desire\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"a very new generation\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1844}, {\"ngram\": \"their own part\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"another chapter\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"more success\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1946}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ambition is still there.\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ambition\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You never think we are going to finish this golden period of sport because it just keeps continuing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this golden period\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grainger was speaking in Salford at the launch of 'Find Your Greatness', a new campaign to unearth futureOlympiansand Paralympians.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2090, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Grainger\", \"score\": 0.9999966098731132, \"rank\": 3.1628203695607647e-06, \"text\": \"Grainger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Grainger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Grainger\"}, {\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salford\", \"score\": 0.9633945887479682, \"rank\": 0.03644723087328329, \"text\": \"Salford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salford\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the launch\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"Your Greatness\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \", a new campaign\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"futureOlympiansand Paralympians\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nationwide initiative, aimed at 16-24-year-olds, hopes to introduce young athletes to new sports or match their skill sets to disciplines they may not previously have considered or had oppor